				\begin{document}$$C_{it} = \frac{{Dk_{ei} k_{ai} }}{{Cl_{i} \left( {k_{ai} - k_{ei} } \right)}} \left[ {e^{{ - k_{ei} t}} - e^{{ - k_{ai} t}} } \right] + e_{it}$$\end{document}</tex-math><graphic position="anchor" xlink:href="12967_2016_1072_Article_Equa.gif"/></alternatives></disp-formula>where <italic>C</italic><sub><italic>it</italic></sub> is the observed concentration of the i-th subject at time t, <italic>D</italic> is the dose of ceftriaxone, <italic>k</italic><sub><italic>ei</italic></sub> is the elimination rate constant for subject <italic>i</italic>, <italic>k</italic><sub><italic>ai</italic></sub> is the absorption rate constant for subject <italic>i</italic>, <italic>Cl</italic><sub><italic>i</italic></sub> is the clearance for subject <italic>i</italic>, and <italic>e</italic><sub><italic>it</italic></sub> are normal errors. To allow for random variability between subjects, we assumed:<disp-formula id="Equb"><alternatives><mml:math display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>C</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mi>l</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">β</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>b</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:msup></mml:mrow></mml:math><tex-math id="Equb_TeX">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
